<b>Subject:</b> Some answers for you...txt<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/forum/mithaniel_marr.cgi?read=41" TARGET=_self>Re: Fletcher's shop open for business...txt</A> (Gyrfalcon)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>> I agree that a bow is a worthy weapon for

<BR>&gt; any class that can yield it. My fletching is
<BR>&gt; now 85 and I succeeded on my first Ash Bow
<BR>&gt; (dam 16 range 100 delay 58). I have 2
<BR>&gt; questions regarding fletching and archery.
<P>&gt; 1) Do you put the whittling knife in the
<BR>&gt; fletching kit (I believe this is true
<BR>&gt; considerig your first post but I want to be
<BR>&gt; sure)
<P>---- yes
<P>&gt; 2) How does the bow range and the arrow
<BR>&gt; range work. Do you add them together to get
<BR>&gt; total range (i.e. a hickory bow range 50 and
<BR>&gt; a Large Nock Arrow range 50 means that your
<BR>&gt; range is 100) Or is it the larger of the 2?
<BR>&gt; the average of the 2? I have been unable to
<BR>&gt; determine this.
<BR>---- a very good question that a GM has not been able to answer yet. I am told that I will be given an answer as soon as they locate the correct information.
<P>&gt; In any event BOWS RULE...
<P>&gt; Gyrfalcon
<BR>Agreed indeed fellow tradesman.
<BR>Good travels,
<BR>Algeran
